{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "name": "Spot-breasted thornbird", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-phacellodomus", "name": "Phacellodomus", "latinName": "Phacellodomus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Phacellodomus（Phacellodomus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联9种鸟类，如Rufous-fronted thornbird、Streak-fronted thornbird、Little thornbird等9种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 9, "x": -443.97, "y": -295.69, "z": -16.61}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "name": "Spot-breasted thornbird", "latinName": "Phacellodomus maculipectus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Spot-breasted thornbird（Phacellodomus maculipectus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Spot-breasted thornbird。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -429.69, "y": -333.06, "z": 655.35}, {"id": "bird-spot-breasted-thornbird-4ebac0ac", "name": "Spot-breasted thornbird", "englishName": "Spot-breasted thornbird", "latinName": "Phacellodomus maculipectus", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The spot-breasted thornbird (Phacellodomus maculipectus) is a species of bird in the Furnariinae subfamily of the ovenbird family Furnariidae. It is found in Argentina and Bolivia. Taxonomy and systematics The spot-breasted thornbird was long considered a subspecies of the freckle-breasted thornbird (P. striaticollis), but the two are not closely related. The spot-breasted and the greater thornbird (P. ruber) are sister species. The spot-breasted thornbird is monotypic. Description The spot-breasted thornbird is 17 to 18 cm (6.7 to 7.1 in) long and weighs about 19 to 26 g (0.67 to 0.92 oz). It is a medium-sized thornbird. The sexes have the same plumage. Adults have a light brownish supercilium that extends beyond the eye and an indistinct dull brown stripe behind the eye on an otherwise light brownish face. Their crown is rufous-brown with whitish streaks, their back dull reddish brown, and their rump and uppertail coverts a slightly paler reddish brown. Their wings are mostly shades of brown with darker brown primary coverts and flight feathers with rufous edges and dusky tips. Their tail's central pair of feathers are dull rufescent brown and the rest dull rufous. Their throat is dingy whitish, their breast dark brownish with conspicuous white speckles, their belly brownish white, and their flanks and undertail coverts darkish gray-brown. Their iris is gray, their maxilla blackish to brownish, their mandible gray, and their legs and feet gray to greenish gray. Distribution and habitat The spot-breasted thornbird is found from the Bolivian departments of Cochabamba and Santa Cruz south into northern Argentina as far as La Rioja Province. It inhabits dry to somewhat humid montane woodland (e.g. Alnus and Podocarpus) and scrublands. In elevation it mostly ranges between 1,000 and 2,500 m (3,300 and 8,200 ft) but occurs locally as high as 3,100 m (10,200 ft). Behavior Movement The spot-breasted thornbird is a year-round resident throughout its range. Feeding The spot-breasted thornbird feeds on adult and larval arthropods. It usually forages in pairs. It captures prey by gleaning from the ground or from vegetation as high as the forest's understorey. Breeding The spot-breasted thornbird breeds in the austral spring and summer, starting in September. It builds a cylindrical nest of thorny sticks that can be about 30 cm (1 ft) high and lines an interior chamber with grass. It hangs the nest near the end a tree branch, usually 3 to 4 m (10 to 13 ft) above the ground. The clutch size is usually three eggs. The incubation period, time to fledging, and details of parental care are not known. Vocalization The spot-breasted thornbird's song is \"10–25 less evenly spaced, complaining notes, 'kew, kééé-keee-keee-keee-keee-keeh…' \". Its alarm call is \"a series of squeaky ticking notes\". Status The IUCN has assessed the spot-breasted thornbird as being of Least Concern. It has a fairly large range and an unknown population size that is believed to be stable. No immediate threats have been identified. It is considered fairly common to uncommon and occurs in at least one protected area. References", "shortSummary": "The spot-breasted thornbird (Phacellodomus maculipectus) is a species of bird in the Furnariinae subfamily of the ovenbird family Furnariid…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2e/Phacellodomus_maculipectus_-_Spot-breasted_Thornbird.jpg/960px-Phacellodomus_maculipectus_-_Spot-breasted_Thornbird.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-phacellodomus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-phacellodomus", "species": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus"}, "expandable": true, "x": -429.69, "y": -333.06, "z": 647.14}], "links": [{"key": "bird-spot-breasted-thornbird-4ebac0ac__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "source": "bird-spot-breasted-thornbird-4ebac0ac", "target": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-phacellodomus", "source": "taxonomy-species-phacellodomus-maculipectus", "target": "taxonomy-genus-phacellodomus", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Spot-breasted thornbird 属于属 Phacellodomus。"}]}
